## Rules for Building UI

### 1. Always start with shared classes

Every card-like element MUST use `.card` as its base class. Add modifiers for behavior:

```html
<div class="card card--interactive forum-category-card">
  <div class="card card--interactive card--store product-card">
    <div class="card grengo-create-form"></div>
  </div>
</div>
```

### 2. Component CSS handles layout only

Component-specific CSS files should contain ONLY:

- Layout properties: `display`, `flex-direction`, `gap`, `height`, `width`, `max-width`, `overflow`
- Positioning: `position`, `top`, `left`, `z-index`, `margin`
- Animations: `animation`, `@keyframes`
- Component-specific transforms on hover (e.g. `transform: translateY(-8px) scale(1.02)`)

Component CSS must NOT redeclare:

- `background-color` (use card tokens or override via CSS variable)
- `border` / `border-radius` (inherited from `.card` / `.section`)
- `box-shadow` (inherited from `.card`)
- `padding` (inherited from `.card` unless layout requires override, then set explicitly)
- `cursor: pointer` (use `.card--interactive`)

### 3. Theme compliance

- All colors MUST come from CSS custom properties — never hardcode hex values
- Use `var(--border-color)` not `rgba(0,0,0,0.07)`
- Use `var(--shadow)` not `0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.08)`
- The `data-theme` attribute on `<html>` toggles light/dark

### 4. Responsive behavior

- Use `.grid-2` / `.grid-3` / `.grid-4` for responsive card layouts
- Cards in grids should not set their own width; let the grid control it
- Use `max-width` on cards only when they appear outside a grid

### 5. Hover states

The `.card--interactive:hover` provides: elevated shadow, border highlight, subtle lift. Component CSS may add additional transforms (scale, larger translateY) but must not redeclare shadow or border-color on hover.

### 6. Status feedback

Use semantic tokens: `--error-color`, `--error-bg`, `--success-color`, `--success-bg`, `--warning-color`, `--warning-bg`.

